  "texts": [
    "Thus, EM Acc concludes the lower-bound of the effectiveness of transpilers.Computational Accuracy (CA): It computes the ratio that the translated programs can produce the same execution result as the ground truths, given the same inputs.",
    "Thus, this metric considers the semantic equivalency of programs, which can be formally defined as:𝐶𝐴 = 𝑁 𝑘=1 𝑐𝑎(𝑦 𝑘, ŷ𝑘) 𝑁, where 𝑐𝑎(𝑦 𝑘, ŷ𝑘) = 1 𝐸𝑥𝑒𝑐 𝑘 (𝑦 𝑘) = 𝐸𝑥𝑒𝑐 𝑘 ( ŷ𝑘) 0 𝐸𝑥𝑒𝑐 𝑘 (𝑦 𝑘) ≠ 𝐸𝑥𝑒𝑐 𝑘 ( ŷ𝑘)(2)where 𝑁, 𝑦 𝑘, and ŷ𝑘 carry the same meaning as those in EM Acc, 𝐸𝑥𝑒𝑐 𝑘 (•) denotes the execution result of a program with the test suite of the 𝑘-th sample.",
    "For example, even if 𝑦 𝑘 and ŷ𝑘 are not identical literally, they are considered a correct translation in CA, as long as 𝐸𝑥𝑒𝑐 𝑘 (𝑦 𝑘) = 𝐸𝑥𝑒𝑐 𝑘 ( ŷ𝑘).",
